    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level for a Medium model risk assessment. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is mitigated by conservative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96) and the mandatory quasi-static nature of ASTM F1717. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria. The validation evidence base, including N=11 constructs across two independent laboratories and full uncertainty quantification per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.4, provides sufficient credibility to support regulatory submission. Decision: Accepted with documented gap in Test conditions factor.",
